    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-26T04:46:37+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-26T04:46:37+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-25T19:16:37Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-25T19:16:37Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A strong high pressure system over the Tasman Sea will maintain a ridge over SA. A trough over the southeast of the state will weaken and clear to the east early Sunday. A new high pressure system will develop in the Bight on Sunday, drifting east early next week to merge with the strong high in the Tasman Sea.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW013" description="North West Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-04-26T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-27T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-25T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-26T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">The chance of morning fog in the far west. The chance of a thunderstorm south of Woomera in the early morning. Sunny afternoon. Winds south to southeasterly 20 to 30 km/h. Daytime maximum temperatures in the mid to high 20s.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">##</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-27T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-28T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-26T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-27T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. The chance of morning fog south of Coober Pedy. Winds south to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending east to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h in the morning then becoming light in the late evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 9 and 13 with daytime temperatures reaching the mid to high 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-28T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-29T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-27T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-28T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Winds east to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending north to northeasterly 15 to 25 km/h during the morning then tending east to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 11 and 14 with daytime temperatures reaching around 30.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-29T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-30T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-28T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-29T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Winds east to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending north to northeasterly 20 to 30 km/h during the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to between 13 and 17 with daytime temperatures reaching around 30.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
